news24h.headline: Gold Price Rebounds as US Passes OBBB
Gold futures opened at $3,350 per ounce Wednesday, up 0.4% from Tuesday's close
Gold prices add to weekly recovery and consolidate around $3,340-$3,350 band
Gold fell to 3,352.49 USD/t.oz on July 3, 2025, down 0.15% from the previous day
Fed rate cut expectations revive as core CPI data comes in softer than expected
Goldman Sachs predicts gold to reach $3,700 by year-end 2025
Tariff deadline approaches as Trump suggests he won't extend tariff pause
Gold ETF holdings increased by 3.88 million ounces this year to 86.7 million ounces
Central banks doubled annual gold purchases from 500 to over 1,000 metric tonnes since 2022
US Dollar stages modest bounce from three-and-a-half-year low

analysis.fedImpact: Fed governors suggest possible July rate cut with core CPI coming in softer than expected, supporting gold's safe-haven appeal amid monetary policy uncertainty

technicalView.keyLevels: Consolidating around $3,340-$3,350 band with resistance at $3,358 and support at $3,300

analysis.priceTarget: Range-bound between $3,300-$3,400 with potential breakout above $3,400 on sustained bullish momentum
analysis.currencyImpact: USD weakness from 3.5-year lows supports gold, though modest USD bounce creates near-term headwinds
analysis.summary: Gold consolidates after recent rally with neutral bias. Strong institutional flows and Fed dovish signals offset by USD bounce. Watch July 9 tariff deadline and upcoming NFP data for direction.
